{"tree":{"type":"node","kind":"SOURCE_FILE","width":20,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"LET_BINDING","width":20,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"let","width":3},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"IDENT_PATTERN","width":1,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"x","width":1}]},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"=","width":1},{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"APPLY_EXPR","width":12,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"WHITESPACE","text":" ","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","width":4,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"expr","width":4}]},{"type":"node","kind":"LIST_EXPR","width":7,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"[","width":1},{"type":"node","kind":"APPLY_EXPR","width":5,"children":[{"type":"node","kind":"ERROR","width":1,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"@","width":1}]},{"type":"node","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","width":4,"children":[{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"attr","width":4}]}]},{"type":"token","kind":"IDENT_EXPR","text":"]","width":1}]}]}]}]},"diagnostics":[{"kind":{"id":"E0020","name":"missing-binary-operand","expected":"left operand for @","found":{"kind":"@","text":"@"},"fix":"add an expression before the operator","hint":"Binary operators like +, -, *, =, etc. require both a left and right operand.\n\nFor example:\n  ```ocaml\n  let x = 1 + 2   (* correct *)\n  let y = 1 +     (* missing right operand *)\n  let z = + 2     (* missing left operand *)\n  ```\n\nIf you want to create a partially applied operator function, use parentheses:\n  ```ocaml\n  let add_one = (+) 1\n  ```\n"},"span":{"start":15,"end":19}}]}
